The paper discusses the use of computers in mathematics, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). It also mentions the need for efficient integration of different aspects of mathematics, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper briefly surveys the state of the art in mathematical software systems, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE).
